---
description: "This rule provides standards for how to generate or update documentation for the project."
tags: [docs]
alwaysApply: true
---

- Never update system documentation located in the `docs/system` directory.
- Be vary of creating new documentation or updating existing documentation at all. Only create documentation when it is explicitly requested.
- When creating new documentation, always create it in the `docs/` directory.
- Documentation when explicitly requested should be concise and to the point, not overly verbose.
- Do not include any examples or code snippets in the documentation unless explicitly requested or absolutely necessary.
